<section class="sbp-section sbp-section--card sbp-faq" id="SbpFaq">
  <div class="sbp-container sbp-faq__inner">

    <div class="sbp-faq__header">
      <span class="sb-eyebrow">Questions</span>
      <h2 class="sbp-section-headline">Frequently asked.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="sbp-faq__grid">

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">When should I drink it?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>Many customers drink it as a morning ritual alongside or instead of Wizard's Brew. Others use it as an afternoon or evening wind-down — it is caffeine-free and naturally calming. There is no wrong time. Listen to your body.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">Is the curcumin actually absorbed?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>Yes — we made sure of it. Curcumin is notoriously poorly absorbed on its own. We include black pepper extract which research shows can enhance curcumin absorption by up to 2000%. We also use turmeric juice extract rather than powder which preserves a wider range of active compounds.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">Is it caffeinated?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>No. Golden Latte is naturally caffeine-free making it suitable as an afternoon or evening drink or for people who prefer to avoid caffeine entirely.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">Can I take both Golden Latte and Wizard's Brew?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>This is actually how Spellbinder is designed to be used — as a two-elixir system. Wizard's Brew handles energy, cognition, hormonal adaptability, and longevity. Golden Latte adds deep inflammatory support, immune breadth, and recovery. Together they are significantly more powerful than either one alone.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">How do I prepare it?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>Add one scoop to 8–12 oz of hot water or warm milk. Stir or froth. Add honey if desired. It froths exceptionally well — a milk frother takes it to café level in 30 seconds.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="sbp-faq__item">
        <summary class="sbp-faq__trigger">
          <span class="sbp-faq__question">Is it vegan and dairy-free?</span>
          <span class="sbp-faq__caret"><svg width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L6 6L11 1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="sbp-faq__answer">
          <p>Yes. Golden Latte is vegan and dairy-free. Add whatever milk you prefer — oat, almond, coconut, or whole milk all work beautifully.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

